Port of Locale::Wolowitz from Perl. Pylocwolitz is a very imple text localization system, meant to be used by web applications (but can pretty much be used anywhere). Yes, another localization system.

Example:
    i18n.loc('hello', 'es'), 'Hola')
    i18n.loc('welcome %(name)s', 'se', {'name': 'hobbestigrou'}),

See documentation on readthedocs http://pylocwolowitz.readthedocs.org/en/latest/
